song.embed_content: Read “Sensitive” by Dreamer Isioma on Genius
song.title: Sensitive

annotations: [Intro]

Sensitive is a song by originally the name Serena Isiomia as you can hear her name in the intro.

The song is basically about how this generation or this era of the world we are currently in the people are sensitive. As of the repeatedly chorus as Isiomia says, “How you gon' feel when I go take your bitch, nigga? And I don’t mean your chick. Bitches these days are so sensitive.”. She stating how currently people are getting more offended by the word ‘Bitch’ especially to women. The song also mentions Serena’s lover and how her lover is “rocking Christian Dior” that she bought her and also how shes fucking her and now shes addicted to their sex. Serena also mentions the government a few times and how they are her opps because of how the government takes money from people and how she wants to repay her people back by “fixing the broken streets”

This song is an upbeat and flowy sound, would be amazing for a summer car ride with the windows down. A very catchy song that never gets overplayed.
Christian Dior
Serena is going to be able to provide for her lover, having the means to act out the fantasy of dressing him in luxury clothing.
Bitches these days are so sensitive

This reoccurring line within the song projects Dreamer’s view of contemporary existence and he critiques the way people care beyond necessity. Contextually the listener infers that the whole cancel culture which is on the rise currently bothers Dreamer and highlights that people need to let go. In a ‘The Lemonade Stand’ interview, Dreamer explained that her rapid fame seemed unreal, and it made their  ‘existential’. Thus, they perhaps wants to highlight that life is so surreal and crazy that we just need to live it without being so sensitive and getting worked up unnecessarily…
I lay her down in my BDG ripped jeans
BDG jeans are trendy jeans sold at Urban Outfitters
